  "texts": [
    "The adaptive learning algorithms could dynamically modify their operational parameters in real time to mitigate errors, resulting in a performance increase of approximately 30% in precision-dependent tasks [14]- [16].",
    "Such adaptivity not only helps in reducing the propagation of errors, but also ensures that the system continually evolves in response to new data, making it particularly relevant for the dynamic environments in which LLMs operate [15], [17], [18].",
    "Automated Feedback MechanismsAutomated feedback mechanisms have been extensively researched, particularly for their efficacy in educational technologies.",
    "Those systems operate by automatically assessing outputs and providing immediate corrective feedback, significantly reducing the need for human intervention [19], [20].",
    "Some studies highlighted their use in language learning platforms, where automated corrections and adaptive feedback mechanisms significantly improved user engagement and learning outcomes, suggesting similar potential benefits for automated error correction in LLMs [21]- [23]."
